    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Eps15 regulates GluA1 surface expression in neurons\"\nFig.4: \"Eps15 regulates basal AMPAR endocytic trafficking\"\nFig.5: \"Eps15 regulates glutamate-induced AMPAR endocytic trafficking\"\nFig.6: \"Eps15 and GluA1 interaction is ubiquitin-dependent\"\nFig.7: \"GluA1 ubiquitination is required for Eps15 association\"\nFig.8: \"Nedd4 enhances Eps15 association with GluA1\"\nFig.9: \"Eps15-mediated AMPAR internalization is clathrin-dependent\"\n\nLiteral: \"AMPAR internalization begins with an association with the adaptor protein AP2, or Eps15 for the ubiquitinated receptors, followed by the recruitment of clathrin to form clathrin-coated pits. Clathrin interacts with amphiphysin, which then brings in dynamin to subsequently pinch off the coated pits to form endocytic vesicles.\". Experimental description: - \"Primary cultured hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18 rat embryos were cultured onto coverslips as described previously\"\n- Species of overexpressed Eps15 is not stated in the paper.",
